column43:
Green Consumption


Green Consumption can be understood as a purchasing and consumption behavior that has the desirable goal to minimize environmental consequences (Kim et al., 2012). The term "green" can also be viewed as "oriented toward sustainable development" (Peattie, 2010, p.197). A major aspect of green consumption is green food consumption.
